article.description: Brandon Anderson had 11 points, seven rebounds and seven assists as Brown romped past Merrimack 82-55 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Anderson lifts Brown past Merrimack 82-55
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Brandon Anderson had 11 points, seven rebounds and seven assists as Brown romped past Merrimack 82-55 on Wednesday night. Anderson entered the game as the leading scorer in the Ivy League and 10th in the nation at 23.3 points per game. He took just nine shots in the contest, hitting 2 of 4 from long range. Tamenang Choh had 17 points for Brown (5-3). Zach Hunsaker added 13 points and six rebounds. Jaylan Gainey had 7 points and seven blocks for the hosts. Ziggy Reid had 13 points for the Warriors (5-5), who are playing their first season at the Division 1 level. Juvaris Hayes added 10 points and six assists. Brown plays Stony Brook on the road on Saturday. Merrimack plays Army at home next Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
